node.text: @keith.wee Ah yes I understand all you have mentioned. I love what Fujifilm is doing but yeah I’m figuratively married to Canon with 2 primary bodies so may not be the most practical thing to make that 3 haha. Cheers.
I can totally relate to that slippery slope! :)

My first Fujifilm was the X10 in 2013 which I used for a concert, followed by the X20 and the rest was a slippery slope of how X-mount grew and I got acquainted with the users, brand and cameras. Here’s sharing some shots from the X10 and X20 back then, pretty impressive for a brand few were acquainted with back then I feel.
.
.

@limzerui I think pretty interesting when I actually reprocessed those photos too. Worth trying 😆
Wah I gonna see if I can find my X10 and X20 images 🤣

@edhblvd if I didn’t recall wrongly the X10 had a 2/3 in sized sensor back then, not to shabby but of course options have gone way larger too. As u said, an 1 in sensor would have brought them much forward too, since Sony got wildly successful with their RX100 series too.
@keith.wee when they made the X30 with EVF they really should have upgraded the sensor. But the lens would have gotten bigger as well.
I always wished Fujifilm had brought out a 1” sensor X40 with the old optical viewfinder.

@keith.wee That’s all correct. But idk I am kind of doubtful that Fuji would explore creating a X40. If it does come out, I would be very much interested in it.

The X100 series and the Xx0 series were kind of 2 different peas in a pod. The X100 series I would think in sales won out the Xx0.
@melvinqht I don have faith in that we will see a X40 though, even if they don’t use the Xtrans sensor. In a way that’s why some of my friends are holding onto their X10/20s

@keith.wee Ah yes I understand all you have mentioned. I love what Fujifilm is doing but yeah I’m figuratively married to Canon with 2 primary bodies so may not be the most practical thing to make that 3 haha. Cheers.

I had the X20. I loved the concept behind it; it’s physicality of it, it’s image quality was actually pretty good for what it was. The one thing I absolutely loved was the manual zoom mechanism.

I sold it to a friend. But I hope Fuji could make a X40 with a 1” sensor and that manual zoom mechanism.
@photosphere.sg hahah yes bro. I think it’s from Gariz (it’s quite a few years ago and I haven’t gotten to know Kenji yet too)
This half case not from Kenji right?
I can totally relate to that slippery slope! :)
